Unidirectional Pipe Resources in C

1. TutorialsPoint – Inter-Process Communication: Pipes
   Description: This tutorial covers the basics of using pipes for inter-process communication in C, including how to set up a unidirectional pipe between a parent and child process.
   Link: https://www.tutorialspoint.com/inter_process_communication/inter_process_communication_pipes.htm

2. GeeksforGeeks – C Program to Demonstrate fork() and pipe()
   Description: An example demonstrating how to use fork() and pipe() in C to establish communication between processes.
   Link: https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/c/c-program-demonstrate-fork-and-pipe/

3. Codequoi – Pipe: an Inter-Process Communication Method
   Description: This article delves into the use of pipes for inter-process communication, providing a simple explanation and examples.
   Link: https://www.codequoi.com/en/pipe-an-inter-process-communication-method/

4. Beej's Guide to Interprocess Communication
   Description: A comprehensive guide that covers various aspects of inter-process communication, including pipes.
   Link: https://beej.us/guide/bgipc/html/
